  <title>Cogl.PipelineAlphaFunc</title>
  <p>Alpha testing happens before blending primitives with the framebuffer and
gives an opportunity to discard fragments based on a comparison with the
incoming alpha value and a reference alpha value. The <link xref="Cogl.PipelineAlphaFunc"/>
determines how the comparison is done.</p>

<terms>
<item>
<title><code>PipelineAlphaFunc.NEVER</code></title>
  <p>Never let the fragment through.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>PipelineAlphaFunc.LESS</code></title>
  <p>Let the fragment through if the incoming
  alpha value is less than the reference alpha value</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>PipelineAlphaFunc.EQUAL</code></title>
  <p>Let the fragment through if the incoming
  alpha value equals the reference alpha value</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>PipelineAlphaFunc.LEQUAL</code></title>
  <p>Let the fragment through if the incoming
  alpha value is less than or equal to the reference alpha value</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>PipelineAlphaFunc.GREATER</code></title>
  <p>Let the fragment through if the incoming
  alpha value is greater than the reference alpha value</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>PipelineAlphaFunc.NOTEQUAL</code></title>
  <p>Let the fragment through if the incoming
  alpha value does not equal the reference alpha value</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>PipelineAlphaFunc.GEQUAL</code></title>
  <p>Let the fragment through if the incoming
  alpha value is greater than or equal to the reference alpha value.</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>PipelineAlphaFunc.ALWAYS</code></title>
  <p>Always let the fragment through.</p>
</item>
</terms>
